Five South African personalities will be partying it up at an African Getdown party at Elyx House in Hollywood, with guest host, Grammy- and Oscar-winning artist and actor Common The event will include appearances by top South African artists Heavy-K, Anatii and Da LES, as well as TV presenters Luthando “Loot Love” Shosha and Ayanda Thabethe. The invitation-only event follows the recent global success of African-inspired culture in the likes of Black Panther, a number of recent music collaborations between African and American artists and the marquee accomplishments of a number of African and diaspora actors. READ MORE: WATCH: Black Coffee on how to deal with fame “The Elyx House is a venue which hosts only the world’s top talent and, as a brand that supports and stands by African creativity, we are excited that South African talent have been given this opportunity to be exposed to the global entertainment industry,” says Iris Le Berg, Global Marketing Manager at The Absolut Company. “What we want to do is bring contemporary African creativity to the world, while also potentially creating collaborations between US artists and producers with African artists, opening a cultural conversation between the two continents,” says event organiser Davin Phillips of Celebrity Services Africa. – News24 Wire